title: Coming Up Broke
report:
Welcome back to the Jart Report after a week fifteen that brought us two incredible playoff matchups that came down to the wire. Despite Brad’s attack at the expected quality of these reports following the elimination of The Family, we remain committed to bringing you the best coverage in all of fantasy football.

Week 15 Recap

I’ve Got a Half Chubb vs Real Brothers

Prediction: CJ 122.22 - 112.24

Reality: CJ 115.42 - 106.64

Perfect management by CJ and Christian Kirk’s garbage time 29 yard TD while trailing the Lions by 20+ proves the difference here. It seems only fitting that in a year characterized by poor management choices and sticking with Family RBs that probably shouldn’t even have been on the team in the first place (Saquon, Miles), it was the benching of Miles Sanders this week that also cost The Family a chance to advance to the semi-finals. After taking Kyle Pitts at 51st Overall over Mark Andrews, Jart watched Andrews drop 66.8 on him in the two matchups against CJ, a fitting result for his worst draft pick.

While there were a lot of elements at play, it was the late afternoon window that secured CJ the victory, with Aaron Rodgers and Mark Andrews outsourcing Ja’Marr Chase, Kyle Pitts, and Davante Adams 54.42 to 23.9. With only 44/268 yards and 1/3 TDs going to Adams from Rodgers, CJ pulled off the rare QB win in an elite QB-WR face off. Second half production from Chubb and steady contributions from RIP Dmont and Diontae Johnson were enough to hold off an attempted torrid comeback from proven NFL QB Jalen Hurts. A fun one from two teams that can be pleased with the efforts they put forth, unless it’s Michael Pittman or Ja’Marr Chase.

What The League Thought:

-CJ rocked

-Folbe and MW and Bank suck at fantasy a lot

-Another tough year for Jart. A good team that just can’t seem to make the jump to glory because of tough roster decisions. Jim Caldwell esque some would say

-CJ managed a perfect game

-Mark Andrews is that ____

-Would have really preferred Jarrett to win, Cj shouldn’t be in the league

CJ: Love playing my guy in the playoffs

Jart: Tough loss, but if I had to lose to someone glad it was CJ. BOL rest of the way.

Aiyuk Kidding Me vs CalAmari Cooper

Prediction: Dmichs 116.52 - 116.34

Reality: Dmichs 114.48 - 97.66

In the beginning of the season, NN’s squad was truly known as Cooper Kupp and then everyone else. In the first round of the playoffs, they got back to playing that way. No one else scored above 15.5, and the final scorer makes this matchup closer than it felt for most of the week following Travis Kelce and Jonathan Taylor’s explosive games on Thursday and Saturday respectively in combining for 59.1 points.

There was not much else to right home about for Dmichs’ team as the next highest scorer was the defense (the sooner Dmichs moves on from Dak the better, although he has a great matchup next week), but they got the job done and that’s all that matters this time of year. There are obviously some COVID concerns moving forward, but for right now it’s all celebration.

What the League Thought:

-Dmichs rocked

-NN deserved what he got

-Nn never had a shot

-Travis Kelce is that ____

-Dmichs in 2 years is already establishing himself as a top 4 manager in this league

Dmichs: Crazy that NN even made the playoffs, his team was so a** beginning of the season, good game.

NN: Folbe and MW and Bank suck at fantasy a lot

League Takes

Agree:

-Our league rocks

-JT is the 🐐

-Brad should go to med school

-Jalen Hurts is the GOAT

-D’Andre Swift was a much bigger loss for Jart than people remember

Neutral:

-Everyone who didn’t make the playoffs or wasnt top 6 in roto (same group of guys) cant say sh*t abt anyone who did make them

Disagree:

-Best 4 teams are NOT left

Jart’s Mailbag

What are you doing after your loss?

Hitting the Sparkling Cider bottle again, working on my sermon for this Sunday, and rooting for CJ to grab his first ring.

How am I supposed to care about football without fantasy implications?

You’re not. If I didn’t play fantasy I would never watch the NFL. Just lock in on Alabama.

Will you lose over or under 25 hours of sleep over the off-season about the Rashaad Penny over Miles Sanders start?

Definitely under. I slept great last night, and honestly I'm not that torn up about it. Would’ve been fun to win but I legitimately enjoy writing the report each week more, and I still get to do that! Proud of Miles though for coming through, love how he’s grinded and hope he gets rewarded with a touchdown soon.

Who should be the commissioner of the league next year (if you could just pick)?

Who is our commissioner currently, is it Merrill or Aross? Honestly I don’t think it matters much, we seem to be a solid democracy these days that just loves to yell at our commissioners. I think it should be Nooni because he seems like a good impartial party.

Is it gonna snow for Christmas?

Somewhere, definitely. I’ll break it up into three categories:

3911 Shellmarr Ln: Yes, and a little bit of it should stick.

Chicago: Looking like yes but it probably won’t stick.

Lincoln: No sir, gonna be too warm and no precipitation expected.

Jonah and Alex are the only two members alive with previous titles. Can CJ or Dmichs get it done?

They certainly can. I don’t think it’s out of the question that we see a CJ-Dmichs championship, ensuring that that would be the case. If I had to choose someone to win right now it would certainly be JL, but I like CJ to be in the finals. So JL is my first choice, but CJ and Dmichs are 2 and 3 (no particular order at the time of this writing).

Now that your season is over how will you be spending your Sundays?

I still have four leagues left to sweat the playoffs for! I usually go grocery shopping during the first half of the early window games, and I will likely continue that. Until all my teams are out I will keep watching, but I will probably just have it on my laptop while I play PS5 or something. Either way, there are still a lot of family members out there still playing in greener pastures currently. We are rooting for you Deebo, Beta Metcalf, Davie J, RIP DMONT, and Hollywood!

Should the league implement a mask mandate in the group chat?

In order to ensure we stay under 1k deaths, this does seem like the most logical move. It’s this kind of forward thinking that seems absurd at the time but we’ll look back on and say thank you Merrick Bank for this suggestion.

League member most likely to quit the corporate world and start their own business?

I’ll take CJ, with something in the sports world. I think he’ll end up coaching baseball in some capacity some day, and with that start up a sports business that he loves. My dark horse candidate is Nooni, who I think will be done with the grind and ready to do something new.

What’s your least favorite fast food restaurant?

Um if we’re talking restaurants that I am at sometimes, it would probably be Runza. It’s a Nebraskan thing, and well it is just not as good as anywhere else in my opinion but a lot of my friends who were born and raised here swear by it. I do hate Burger King though besides chicken fries.

Which league member got screwed the hardest this year?

I think this one probably comes down to Jason or myself. Jason lost the single most important player in Derrick Henry, and also dealt with Alvin Kamara missing considerable time as well. Russell Wilson missed considerable time (although he hadn’t been amazing), and so Jason getting to 7-7 with all of that was quite the feat. For me, losing Saquon Barkley, D’Andre Swift, and Miles Sanders were all big losses that left my RB depth very small very quickly. Davante Adams missed a game due to covid as well. Overall though, I think Jason was more screwed over by injuries, but I also had the highest roto SOS by a considerable margin. So I think it’s one of the two of us, you can decide what you categorize screwed as.

Would you want your future kid(s) to attend Nebraska or UofM?

I think this will probably come down to where I am living at that point in time (see next question). Given that I will likely never make very much money, if they can get in-state tuition, we taking it. I think over time where one attends undergrad really won’t make a massive deal, and so I’d probably lean Nebraska even though it obviously is not as good of a school academically. Since my kids will be raised Nebraska fans I’d want them to get to experience being at the school they grew up loving for four years.

Where will each member live by age 30? Age 80?

I feel ill-equipped to answer this question because I don’t know anyone’s imminent travel plans or career aspirations. So I will say that everyone is staying in the state they are currently, with the exception of Folbe heading to California to work for Anduril and MW is in New York. I will be living somewhere else in all likelihood but I have no idea where yet.

By age 80, I like MW, Folbe, Brad, and Bank to be living in Florida. Alex and Dmichs in California, JL in Vegas, Jart in Nebraska, NN, Jase, and CJ in Michigan, Nooni in a foreign country.

Life expectancy of each league member?

I am not about to actually do this, so I will instead do how many years off their life they lost from the stress of fantasy football this season, from least to most years lost:

12. JL

11. Aross

10. Nooni

9. MW

8. CJ

7. Jason

6. Dmichs

5. Bank

4. NN

3. Folbe

2. Jart

1. Brad

What age will each league member get married?

I have absolutely zero idea, so my official stance is that no one is ever getting married, eleven of us are already married to the game and Brad is married to the grind, or at least talking about the grind.

If you had to use one word to describe the remaining teams, what would it be?

Jonah: Consistent

Alex: Opportunistic

CJ: Gritty

Dmichs: Elite

Now that your season has ended, what Family member are you most proud of, which one are you most indifferent to, and which one are you most disappointed in?

Proud: Jalen Hurts. Dude fought back from his high ankle sprain and played an almost flawless game, putting the Eagles into the playoffs as of this week.

Indifferent: Kyle Pitts. He’s a lot better than his production showed, but got doubled often due to Calvin Ridley being out. Was tough to watch him all year.

Disappointed: Ja’Marr Chase. After an incredible first half of the season, Chase was atrocious outside of a Week 14 where I did not need his production. 1 catch for 3 yards in the playoffs?

Is Michigan-Georgia going to be played?

Yes. Way too much money in it for it not to happen, I genuinely think they will delay if need be.

What is the league missing?

Structure that creates some sort of carry-over between seasons. While relegation isn’t necessarily an option, and dynasty seems to be too polarizing of a topic currently, a keeper or two or being able to trade future draft picks (or perhaps draft $$) would create some sense of continuation. We could certainly walk through restrictions on these to avoid issues, but the existence of one or both of these would allow for more of a true owner feel, something I think the league would benefit from.

On To The Semi-Finals!

The Lopas Sportsbook Official Futures Odds:

JL +300 → +265

Aross +400 → +420

Jart +450

NN +500

Dmichs +550 → +400

CJ +650 → +350

What We Said Last Week on the Odds: Obviously, the worst value here is Jart, who has played erratic football, and needs to win three games to win the league. Considering Aross has essentially the same odds and only needs to win two, we like his value much better. If we were a betting man, we’d take JL, but we like the value on Dmichs as well. Expect the winner of JL-Dmichs to win the league.

Our Thoughts This Week on the Odds: The book continues to fade Aross despite his solid positioning currently, so as long as he continues to find ways to win we love his value. We still expect the winner of Dmichs-JL to win the league though, so put half your savings on one and half on the other!
